
# Copilot Web Dev – 8-Week Learning Prompts & Quizzes

Keep this file in your project root (e.g., `/learning/`) and open it in VS Code. Use **Markdown Preview** (`Ctrl/Cmd + Shift + V`).

---

## Week 1: HTML, CSS, JavaScript Basics
**Videos**
- Introduction to HTML CSS JavaScript – Tutorial #1 (YouTube) – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EDJ9YbHXRZA
- Build a Simple Website with HTML, CSS, JavaScript – Course for Beginners (YouTube) – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=krfUjg0S2uI
- HTML CSS and Javascript Website Design Tutorial - Beginner Project Fully Responsive (YouTube) – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FazgJVnrVuI

**Copilot Prompts**
- `// Create a semantic HTML layout with header, nav, main, section, aside, footer`
- `// CSS: build a responsive 12-col grid with gap and fluid images`
- `// JS: add a dark-mode toggle using CSS variables and localStorage`
- `// Build a card component with hover animation and accessible focus styles`

**Quiz (answer in code/comments)**
1. What does the `<section>` element represent vs `<div>`?
2. Name three semantic HTML tags and typical use.
3. In `.card { display: grid; gap: 1rem; }`, what does `gap` control?
4. Class vs id selectors—when to use each?
5. What is the DOM? Show reading & updating text via JS.
6. JS to toggle a class `open` on `<body>` from a button `#toggle`.
7. How to open links in a new tab safely (`target` + security attr)?
8. `==` vs `===` example.
9. CSS box model essentials.
10. Why `defer` when including external JS?

