## Week 2: Responsive Design & Accessibility
**Videos**
- A Practical Guide to Responsive Web Design – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x4u1yp3Msao
- Responsive Web Design Crash Course – Flexbox, Grid & Accessibility – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ipBhj3F5hqI
- Learn Accessibility – Full a11y Tutorial – https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e2nkq3h1P68

**Copilot Prompts**
- `// CSS: mobile-first layout with breakpoints at 600px and 960px`
- `// Build an accessible hamburger nav with aria-expanded & keyboard support`
- `// Implement prefers-color-scheme dark mode with CSS variables`
- `// Add focus-visible styles for interactive elements`

**Quiz**
1. Define mobile-first CSS and benefits.
2. Pick breakpoints for 3→1 column and justify.
3. CSS to ensure images scale without overflow.
4. ARIA roles—2 examples and usage.
5. Keyboard-accessible hamburger menu (key events).
6. CSS snippet for `prefers-color-scheme`.
7. Two ways to ensure color contrast & testing approach.
8. What does `:focus-visible` do? Provide CSS.
9. Accessible label + input HTML.
10. Quick devtools steps to test responsiveness.

